sentences: Zach Brock (born August 2, 1974) is an American jazz violinist and composer.
He was a member of Snarky Puppy from 2007 to 2011 and  in 2016.
He was a member of Snarky Puppy from 2007 to 2011 and  in 2016.
He graduated from Bryan Station High School in 1992, before attending Northwestern Universityâ€™s Bienen School of Music, majoring in performance violin.
During his sophomore year at Northwestern, while bicycling through a busy intersection, he was struck by a hit-and-run driver.
More than three years of surgeries and rehabilitation from the accident set back his formal studies.
Despite the delay, he graduated in 1999.
For several years after the turn of the century, Brock led and recorded with his quartet, Zach Brock and the Coffee Achievers, releasing three albums between 2003 and 2007.

Around 2008 Brock became a member of two different bands with which he continues to be associated.

He departed Snarky Puppy in 2011 for other projects, including touring with Stanley Clarke, but he returned to the band in 2016 and continues to be one of now Brooklyn-based band's most frequent performers, including on two of the band's Grammy Award winning albums.
